body:
First of all, thanks for making ReactJS, and spreading its core ideas to others.

Anyway, the gist of this issue is : how about separating out 
- https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/master/src/renderers/dom/shared/CSSProperty.js
- https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/master/src/renderers/dom/shared/CSSPropertyOperations.js
- (+ other files for styling?)
into another npm module?

Here's my situation:
I'm using RxJS + React for animation, and I'm using a direct-to-dom method for performance. I did it by creating a 'StyleStreamedComponent' which can be used like this:
```typescript
<StyleStreamedComponent
   tagName="div"
   styleStream={animationStream  // 0 ~ 1. follows timer / scroll / whatever I like.
      .map((x => {
         const opacity: tween.power3(x);
         return {
            transform: `translate(0, ${x * window.innerHeight * 0.5})`,
            opacity, 
         }
      });
   }
>
   <h1> animation here. </h1>
</StyleStreamedComponent>
```

For the StyleStreamedComponent implementation, I'm resorting to a disgusting hack as I'm not very fond of importing a reactJS-internal code:
```typescript
export class StyleStreamedComponent {
    componentDidMount() {
        this.styleSubscription = this.props.styleStream
            .subscribe((newStyle) => 
                // save this.style in case of re-render.
                this.style = Object.assign(this.state.style, newStyle);
                _.forEach(newStyle, (value, key) => {
                     if (_.includes(requirePxStyles, key)) {
                         if (value.constructor == Number) {
                             targetDOM.style[key] = `${value}px`;
                             return;
                         }
                    }
               targetDOM.style[key] = value;
        });
    }
```

ps: separating out those CSS-utility functionalities into a npm module might be helpful to other library-maintainers/authors as well.
